# User config (contains personal data — author name, site URLs, publishing targets)
# NOTE: If you run on GitHub Actions, you have two options:
#   1. Remove config.yaml from this list and commit it (ONLY if it contains no secrets)
#   2. Keep it ignored and generate config.yaml from GitHub Secrets in a workflow step
# NEVER put API keys in config.yaml — those belong in .env.local / GitHub Secrets.
config.yaml
voice-guidelines.md

